Student Environment Setup Guide
Java Backend Development using Spring Boot


1.	Install Java (JDK 17) 
Download JDK 17 from the official website of Oracle JDK.  (Java 17 - jdk-17_windows-x64_bin.msi)
After installation, Java will be installed in the following location:
C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-17
•	Configure JAVA_HOME
1. Right click This PC
2. Click Properties
3. Select Advanced System Settings
4. Click Environment Variables
Under System Variables → New
Variable Name : JAVA_HOME
Variable Value : C:\Program Files\Java\jdk-17
Click OK.
•	Add Java to PATH
1. In System Variables, select Path → Edit
2. Click New
3. Add the following entry:
%JAVA_HOME%\bin
Click OK.
•	Verify Java Installation
Open Command Prompt and run:
java -version
javac -version
Expected output should display Java version 17.


2.	Install Apache Maven
Download Apache Maven Binary ZIP 
Maven 3.x.x - Download Apache Maven – Maven : 
Binary zip archive	apache-maven-3.9.12-bin.zip
Do NOT download source archive.
and extract it to: C:\Program Files\Apache\Maven
Create a new system variable:
Variable Name : MAVEN_HOME
Variable Value : C:\Program Files\Apache\Maven
Add Maven to the system PATH:
%MAVEN_HOME%\bin
Verify installation:
mvn -version


